Publications Per Day Plot

nytDat %>%
  mutate(pubDay = gsub("T.*",
                       "",
                       response.docs.pub_date)) %>%
  group_by(pubDay) %>%
  summarise(count=n()) %>%
  filter(count >= 2) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(aes(x=reorder(pubDay, count), 
               y=count), 
           stat="identity") + 
  coord_flip() +
  labs(title = "NYT Publications Per Day with 'honeybee' in the publication")

Below, I create a word frequency plot without using stop words, stemmed key terms, or removing numbers. This is for comparison so that I know that my processing of the tokenized data outputs as expected, changing the distribution of word frequencies.

data(stop_words)

tokenized <- tokenized %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) #removes the stop words 
## Joining, by = "word"
tokenized %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  filter(n > 10) %>%
  mutate(word = reorder(word, n)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(n, word)) +
  geom_col() +
  labs(y = NULL,
       title = "Frequency of words co-occuring with 'honeybee' in NYT publications")
